stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> FREE

    FREE --> GRANTED: acquire S/X or mutex owner set
    GRANTED --> RELEASED: release owner cleared
    RELEASED --> FREE: no waiter

    GRANTED --> WAITING: conflict and caller may wait
    WAITING --> GRANTED: grant after owner release
    WAITING --> TIMEOUT: wait budget exhausted
    WAITING --> VICTIM: row lock deadlock victim only

    GRANTED --> CONVERTING: lifecycle S requests X
    CONVERTING --> GRANTED: conversion granted
    CONVERTING --> TIMEOUT: conversion timeout

    TIMEOUT --> RELEASED: cleanup pins and wait slots
    VICTIM --> RELEASED: rollback releases transaction locks
    RELEASED --> [*]

    note right of WAITING
        Row locks enter Wait-For Graph.
        Undo page latch, history mutex, rseg mutex,
        and tablespace lifecycle waits use ordered short waits or timeout.
    end note

    note right of CONVERTING
        Undo tablespace truncation must not convert while holding
        record locks, page latches, or history list mutex.
    end note

    note right of VICTIM
        Only transaction row/gap/next-key waits can become VICTIM.
        Purge workers back off instead of joining transaction deadlock detection.
    end note
